	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f106796607012089">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">Shaman vs Mage</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Nov 4th 12:14 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=271291"><span id=" ">Jrrazor</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">7 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Having spent endless hours in VT, and i must say that this is the most absolute boringest zone i've ever had the displeasure of adventuring through. <br/><br/>However, VT is a necessary evil in gearing up for the Elemental Planes. The resists and AC on most of the items dropped in VT are still much better than the majority of the items dropping in Teirs 1-3. I'm not saying that ALL of the loot that drops in VT is better, just the majority. Another thing about VT verses POP is that in VT, named mobs drop 4 items of loot everytime, verses POP dropping an average of 2 (not counting spells or parchments). This is a whole lot better average of raid to loot ratio (which our guild currently uses to determine winners on loot). This allows a guild to gear it's members up faster than through PoP while at the same time make them more effective in PoP.<br/><br/>Overall, this item would be a tremendous item for anyone to have in their arsenol. Shaman vs. Mage, well, that depends on the guild and the player. I myself being a 65 Shaman (maxxed on all melee stats) could definitely use the item but most of the time i'm Malos'ing then slowing, not worrying about lowering their resists even farther. Once they are slowed, i'm to busy Canning and healing (and that goes for the other 7 Shamans in our guild that are VT keyed). Our Clerics are all maxxed at FT 15. Throw a Bard in the Cleric group and some C5, they would rarely go LOM and would have to ask for Mod Rod even less. <br/><br/>Since Mages, along with Wizards and other high damage DD spell casting classes, generally have to wait for the tank to get a good aggro on a mob before being able to nuke, this neck item would a great item for their arsenol. <br/><br/>So, even as a Shaman, i would be more inclined to let a Mage have the item. Most of the guild mages i know are not even close to maxxing out melee stats and this would be a great item to help them be more durable during those long fights. <br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Nov&nbsp;&nbsp;4 12:23:33 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
